Steinhoff, the world&#8217;s second-biggest furniture retailer after IKEA, reported a 48% jump nine-month sales on Thursday, thanks to a series of acquisitions. The South African-based company has its primary share listing in Frankfurt and a secondary listing in Johannesburg, said sales totalled 14.9 billion euros ($17.69 billion) in the nine months ended June. ($1 = 0.8423 euros) 